      ],
      "source": "https://www.longislandguide.com/visit/calverton/"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "In 1978, more than 1,000 acres of the base were turned into Calverton National Cemetery, the largest and busiest U.S. national cemetery by burials per day.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        15
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Calverton%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 6,
      "text": "A 10,000‑foot runway was built at the plant, allowing most Grumman F‑14 Tomcats and E‑2C Hawkeyes to pass through the base.",
